  "texts": [
    "Whether Clec11a can promote bone health by binding to integrin a11 in response to mechanical stimuli is an extremely interesting question that should be further explored and validated by large-scale and multicenter cutting-edge studies.",
    "Clec11a promotes vertebral mineralization in zebrafish by inhibiting fibroblast activation proteins (Fap or Seprase) (45).",
    "The use of a highly selective inhibitor of Fap significantly upregulates typical Wnt pathway-related genes (45), suggesting that Clec11a promotes bone formation in zebrafish through the Fap-regulated Wnt signaling pathway.",
    "Although this study mainly investigated the interaction between Clec11a and Fap in zebrafish and may therefore provide insights on the role of Clec11a in bone.",
    "Differences in the effect of Clec11a between species must also be considered, such as the effect of Clec11a on the phenotype of mice, as well as the expression pattern, developmental stage, and other factors."
  ],
